ew reflection\nmodel also shows a strong O VIII K-edge (at $14.23$ \\AA). We find that the\nabsorption edge at $\\approx 14$ \\AA\\ present in the data can be described by a\nO VIII K-edge formed due to reflection in the accretion disc and a Ne I K-edge\noriginating mostly in the interstellar medium, mitigating the problem of the\napparent very high neon abundance.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 6 Mar 2014 12:55:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
